sentences.english: The targets vary from fixed target, running game target to flying target.
sentences.chinese: 雙向飛碟或飛靶射擊中使用的靶子。

sentences.english: They visit quite frequently with their flying saucers and invasive experiments.
sentences.chinese: 藉助飛碟及其他侵入的實驗頻繁造訪人類。

sentences.english: Running target and clay-pigeon shooter shall shoot at standing position with both hands holding the gun.
sentences.chinese: 移動靶和飛碟射手採用立姿雙手持槍進行射擊。

sentences.english: I thought Isaw aUFO, but it was really an airplane.
sentences.chinese: 我認爲我看見了飛碟，但實際上那只是一架飛機。

sentences.english: Frisbee players must brush the Frisbee at waist level to do a behind-the-back Frisbee brush.
sentences.chinese: 飛碟選手必須刷牙腰部飛盤做幕後背飛盤刷。

sentences.english: The men have already sold four flight-ready saucers for $1,000 (?570) each.
sentences.chinese: 目前，兩人已賣出了4個飛碟，每個1000美元。

sentences.english: Boy:Well, I was walking down Center Street when a UFO landed.
sentences.chinese: 當一個飛碟着陸的時候，我正在中央大街上散步。

sentences.english: Alexandro Garcia was born in Uruguay in 1970. He began making drawings after seeing a UFO.
sentences.chinese: 1970年生於烏拉圭，在目擊到飛碟後開始畫畫。

sentences.english: Why have UFO abductees been used in genetic experiments?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼飛碟綁架被用於遺傳實驗？
我敢打賭，鍾滿是雙向飛碟。

sentences.english: Throw the Frisbee with friends in the park. Go rollerblading.
sentences.chinese: 和朋友們在公園裏扔飛碟，去滑旱冰。

sentences.english: We’re just hangin’ out, playing a little Frisbee with our friends.
sentences.chinese: 我們只是在一起打發時光，跟朋友們玩飛碟。

sentences.english: In the pictures of aliens , ufo , the yeti , hellboy.
sentences.chinese: 這些異形，飛碟，雪人，地獄小子的照片。

sentences.english: He is so crazy about U.F.O.that he laps up all he can read about it.
sentences.chinese: 他對飛碟極爲着迷，貪婪地閱讀一切有關資料。

sentences.english: Carol was the first member of her skeet-shooting team to get married.
sentences.chinese: 卡羅爾雙向飛碟，她是第一位拍攝團隊結婚。
